WEBVTT

00:03.618 --> 00:04.279
Hi, friends.

00:04.700 --> 00:09.666
Welcome to Perdido Bay Methodist Church's podcast on the Gospel of Matthew.

00:10.047 --> 00:11.109
My name is Scott Hong.

00:11.609 --> 00:12.310
Hi, I'm Dudley.

00:12.330 --> 00:13.292
Thanks for joining us.

00:13.772 --> 00:16.015
Today is Friday, March the 6th.

00:16.256 --> 00:17.077
March the 6th.

00:17.497 --> 00:22.204
And today we're finishing up Jesus' sermon about the end times.

00:22.705 --> 00:26.450
We are reading Matthew chapter 24

00:26.946 --> 00:29.669
verse 15 through verse 35.

00:29.709 --> 00:39.962
This is really a part of extended sermon that Jesus began in the temple, on the temple mount, and now he continues it on the mount of Olives.

00:40.302 --> 00:46.670
Jesus talked about the destruction of the temple, Dudley, and then the disciples, they want to know, what is this going to be?

00:46.690 --> 00:47.972
Give us the time I would.

00:48.733 --> 00:49.794
How would we do ready?

00:50.074 --> 00:50.695
Yeah.

00:51.195 --> 00:52.978
And so Jesus says, you know, just watch.

00:53.278 --> 00:53.799
Beware.

00:53.959 --> 00:56.562
Kind of keep your eyes open, he says, at the beginning.

00:56.802 --> 01:01.910
watch, but then he talks about how they're always going to be wars and rumors and wars.

01:01.930 --> 01:03.151
Don't get upset about that.

01:03.171 --> 01:07.398
He talks about how you're going to be persecuted because your faith in me.

01:07.418 --> 01:11.804
He talks about the desolating sacrilege that's put in the temple.

01:11.864 --> 01:16.070
He talks about coming of his coming again.

01:16.130 --> 01:21.298
When the Son of Man comes again, the end of time, when heaven and earth will pass away,

01:23.298 --> 01:26.824
He talks about all that, but he doesn't give an answer.

01:27.546 --> 01:32.675
He doesn't say what he says, but about that day and hour, no one knows.

01:32.915 --> 01:36.842
Neither the angels of heaven nor the son, but only the father.

01:37.423 --> 01:40.669
And he says, keep awake, keep awake, keep watching, keep awake.

01:41.510 --> 01:43.634
Be like the good servants who

01:44.098 --> 01:52.632
are doing what their master is asking to do, not the bad servant who thinks the master is never coming home, so the bad servant gets drunk and starts beating up the other servants.

01:53.052 --> 01:57.199
And so when the master comes home, he's in trouble, but no, be like the good servant.

01:57.239 --> 02:06.073
Be faithful with what God has given you so that when he comes back, say, yeah, good and faithful servant, well done.

02:06.173 --> 02:09.378
So Dudley, what do you glean from this chapter?

02:09.739 --> 02:11.922
I think that we always want to know

02:12.034 --> 02:38.034
when it's like early in acts they ask Jesus when are you at this time going to restore Israel when is this going to happen and then in this chapter they're saying when is this we want to know maybe to be in control if we feel we have the information we can be in control you know if we know it's going to be this date then I can start getting ready later instead of now and

02:38.498 --> 02:41.521
Yeah, Jesus says, you'll be ready all the time.

02:41.582 --> 02:44.225
Be ready and live faithfully all the time.

02:44.325 --> 02:46.187
Yeah, I think it's like this too.

02:46.227 --> 02:52.094
I was thinking of a conversation I had with someone recently that Jesus says we are born again.

02:52.114 --> 02:54.356
So we're born into a family.

02:54.376 --> 02:56.418
So we take on those family traits.

02:56.499 --> 03:03.026
We look like our parents, our ancestors, and we just become

03:03.938 --> 03:12.690
who we are, and in the first birth, that's just natural, but the second birth is following Jesus, and it says that we walk by faith.

03:12.790 --> 03:17.877
We don't always know every calendar date for everything.

03:17.957 --> 03:20.160
Yeah, we live in the present moment.

03:20.180 --> 03:21.542
We start looking like Jesus.

03:21.602 --> 03:25.187
We start resembling Him, and we're faithful while we do.

03:25.207 --> 03:29.493
We know that this world and the things of this world are gonna come to an end.

03:30.054 --> 03:33.138
And that's actually good news for those who are suffering out.

03:33.250 --> 03:35.713
thinking about the situation I ran now.

03:36.094 --> 03:39.819
And for years, Christians in Iran have been horribly persecuted.

03:39.859 --> 03:41.241
They've been suffering.

03:42.002 --> 03:47.369
And Jesus says, you know, the suffering will one day end.

03:47.389 --> 03:51.014
But meanwhile, be faithful with what I've given you.

03:51.194 --> 03:53.317
Be like the good servants.

03:53.977 --> 03:54.338
Yeah.

03:55.479 --> 04:00.466
I think he's interested in us trusting in him.

04:01.026 --> 04:03.330
listening and looking for his return.

04:03.390 --> 04:08.039
But it's not really our responsibility.

04:08.099 --> 04:14.431
Our responsibility is like you're saying is just to be in with Jesus to be ready when he comes back.

04:14.471 --> 04:22.686
Don't be like beating the other servants or getting into all these squabbles doing these or even trying to affect different change.

04:22.746 --> 04:24.690
We can't affect much change except

04:24.834 --> 04:26.336
what He's empowered us to do.

04:26.637 --> 04:29.400
And so that just calls us to live in a relationship with Him.

04:29.681 --> 04:32.425
Now, I want to know what's happening and I want to know when it's going to happen.

04:32.505 --> 04:32.905
Sure.

04:33.046 --> 04:37.212
But we almost can't unless He just reveals it.

04:37.232 --> 04:39.335
And one day the ultimate revelation is coming.

04:39.455 --> 04:40.917
One day it'll come.

04:40.937 --> 04:50.290
When Jesus talks about the end time, He's not trying to satisfy the curiosity of idle people who just want to sit around, well, tell us what happens.

04:50.434 --> 04:59.428
He is giving the words to encourage his followers and to remind them to be focused on the tasks that he has given.

05:01.110 --> 05:10.044
We were talking before, Dudley, that sometimes tough words are not easy to hear, but Jesus will not sugarcoat truth.

05:10.104 --> 05:19.218
He won't avoid heart truth, but he's telling us this stuff so that we will be ready and prepared and thus experience

05:19.298 --> 05:19.919
life.

05:19.939 --> 05:22.481
I mean, these words are all meant to lead us to life.

05:22.982 --> 05:30.509
Yeah, the hard truth that we need to hear is actually, and we don't like it at the time, but it's actually a safeguard for us.

05:30.609 --> 05:39.559
The hard truth usually is me getting out of a destructive situation or a problem or maybe hurting others.

05:39.979 --> 05:43.022
The hard truth brings a need to change.

05:43.262 --> 05:44.283
It brings a need to change.

05:44.323 --> 05:46.866
So we don't do stupid foolish things like

05:47.202 --> 05:49.425
getting drunk and beating up the other servants.

05:49.445 --> 05:50.286
That's right.

05:50.306 --> 05:54.050
And then being surprised when the Master finally shows up.

05:54.471 --> 06:00.658
You know, it reminds me, because all of this is wrapped in the grace of God and what He's done.

06:00.698 --> 06:06.866
And His grace is saving us, is working on us, and we will ultimately be out of here.

06:07.166 --> 06:09.449
And so that's God's working in us.

06:09.989 --> 06:13.874
I'm reminded of one of my teachers, Ms. Hamilton,

06:14.498 --> 06:17.442
back when I was in school, I was usually doing pretty good.

06:17.482 --> 06:22.788
But in this instance, I had not made a good grade and it was going to affect some things.

06:23.729 --> 06:26.613
And she called me up to her desk and showed me my grades.

06:26.753 --> 06:34.062
And then she, as I was watching, she changed the number and made it a little bit better.

06:34.122 --> 06:40.130
She didn't overdo it, she didn't under, but she gave me something I didn't deserve.

06:40.330 --> 06:43.634
Just a couple of points to

06:45.122 --> 06:49.708
maybe encourage me maybe to keep going on the journey, keep trying something.

06:50.188 --> 06:53.753
She graded me on a curve in that instance.

06:53.773 --> 06:59.060
Yeah, you did deserve it, but she imputed her righteousness onto you.

06:59.080 --> 07:00.321
I deserved worse.

07:00.482 --> 07:00.822
Yeah.

07:01.583 --> 07:05.889
And that's kind of like with Christ, he imputes us, his righteousness on us.

07:05.949 --> 07:09.493
We are, yeah, declared to be God's beloved children.

07:09.533 --> 07:10.194
So

07:10.530 --> 07:13.773
The end times, all this is not something we need to be afraid of.

07:14.214 --> 07:21.621
It's something that, but we need to be aware that it's coming, that the things of this world will pass away.

07:22.082 --> 07:26.146
Heaven and earth will pass away, Jesus says, but my words will not pass away.

07:26.206 --> 07:28.048
Yeah, and that's good news.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.731
It's good to not have to know everything.

07:31.291 --> 07:38.098
Sometimes I was talking with someone who recently, a friend of mine, he's changing jobs.

07:38.658 --> 07:42.763
He's getting better paid, but he's having less responsibility.

07:43.223 --> 07:48.129
This new job, he doesn't have to do this and do that and to know everything.

07:48.729 --> 07:51.573
But he's getting the better paycheck.

07:52.033 --> 07:53.074
And that's similar.

07:53.295 --> 07:54.876
We don't have to know everything.

07:54.896 --> 07:55.697
We don't have to do this.

07:55.797 --> 07:57.339
There's a freedom and joy that comes with it.

07:57.359 --> 08:00.002
And it has a great reward for us, but we don't have to know everything.

08:00.022 --> 08:04.948
It's kind of the same picture, and I'm thankful that I don't have to know everything.

08:04.968 --> 08:06.930
Because if I did, I still probably

08:07.234 --> 08:08.780
would do something to goof it up.

08:09.021 --> 08:09.824
Yeah.

08:09.844 --> 08:12.092
Thank you, Dudley.

08:12.112 --> 08:13.758
And thank you, friends, for listening.

08:14.521 --> 08:15.585
Have a wonderful weekend.

08:16.247 --> 08:17.010
God bless you.

